# Simple Code Philosophy

## Context
- When writing any code
- When reviewing or refactoring existing code
- When adding new features or fixing bugs

## Requirements
- Code must be self-documenting through clear naming
- No comments ever - rewrite unclear code instead
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Break complex functions into smaller, focused functions
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions
- Use type hints for clarity
- Remove verbose docstrings
- No isinstance() checks unless critical for API boundaries
- No try/catch blocks for safety - let it crash with useful errors
- No checking if variables exist before using them
- Use expected format/type directly
- Fail fast and loud - no silent failures

